ndgain-id_infr_04-score.def:
Description: The proportion of the population living in the area where elevation is 5 m or less. It is a simple measure of the population sensitive to coastal risks. 
Rationale: An estimate of the population sensitive to the risks arising from seal-level rise, storm surge and similar effects, which are exacerbated by climate change.
ndgain-id_infr_04-score.name: Population living under 5m above sea level
ndgain-id_infr_04-score.source: Population living in areas where elevation is below 5 meters (% of total; population), WDI
